<br>
I've been holding on since kunark while you or other members of the VI staff have blown sunshine up our arses about having everyone's best interest at heart. I'm sorry...but I just don't believe you any more nor do I have any faith whatsoever that you will put things right.<br>
<br>
Your changes have continually erroded the playability of the warrior character. I currently play my warrior because I'm too damn stubborn to quit after 59 levels and because my guildleader seems to think we need another lvl 60 warrior. So I continue to work on it. We won't need any more lvl 60 warriors once these shields go live.<br>
<br>
As it stands now, I can no longer find pickup groups pretty much at all during the day time on prexus. Even with guildmembers, it's difficult to do while most are at work/school. I can find them in the evening but usually only after waiting for an hour or more.  I'm sure that doesn't seem like a long time for those knights and other classes who used to or still do have to wait for hours for a group. I don't have that luxury...i can usually only play for an hour or two at a time.  As it stands now, I've been reduced to soloing, which I'm only able to do at all because I can two box with my 46 shaman.<br>
<br>
When this shield change goes live, and I say when becuase I feel fairly confident that it will, unless there are major warrior changes in the same patch, I'm done. So are alot of other warriors. I'm done in that I'll close the account my warrior is on and work on my 56 rogue. Others will do the same, play another character, or just slog it out out of sheer stubborness.<br>
<br>
Even if these shields are made to generate insane amounts of agro for warriors,  we will still lose at least 1/3 of our dps output. I'm sorry...but I made a warrior because I wanted to dish out damage as much as I took damage. I wanted to be able to stand there toe to toe with the badguy, spit in his eye and dare him to try to get past me. I gave up any ability to move rapidly or to heal myself and agreed to be totally dependent upon group members to get any experience for the privilege of being able to take this damage, stand there and smile, and give it right back. No matter how good these shields are for warriors, they will still have to be obtained unless the shields we have are retrofitted...oh, wait...we don't have shields. So every warrior who aspires to ever be an mt will be scrambling for the limited amount of shields that every melee will now want. The few decent shields that will be available will only be obtained from mobs I will never encounter and will be camped 24/7 by manaburn teams if they're dropable and uber guilds if they are not. Thus, my character, along with the thousands of other warriors not in a tier1 guild will all be done.<br>
<br>
By the way...I'm sorry Naubi, but you are either completely full of crap or the most clueless Sk I've ever met. I have never, against Any sk, been able to take agro from them unless the either died, feigned or outright Allowed me to. You also may be &quot;end game&quot; but most of us are not. I will never see most of the &quot;right clicky&quot; items you mentioned because manaburn teams won't allow me to, and I don't have the plat to buy them. I will never see SoD or BoC or any of those other little nifty items the tier1 people have been talking about. This is because I don't have time for the commitment necessary to be in a guild capable of getting them, nor do I want to be associtated with the type of loot whore dickheads that tend to find their way into those guilds (and this is no knock on the guilds themselves...they usually are mostly full of great people...but the selfish do tend gravitate towards them like moth's to a flame). Those &quot;little spells&quot; you have that you find so little utility in are the reason you are an sk and Not a warrior. No spells, Warrior...with spells, Hybrid. I'm really sick of the hybrid classes bitching about not being able to tank like warriors. You are not warriors...you have a price for admission...that price is that you lose tanking ability to be able to cast. You want to tank, lose the spells, plain and simple.<br>
<br>
The addition of shields as they are now on test will just further blur the line between knights and warriors in terms of tanking ability and place them even further above warriors as being more desireable both in xp groups and in raid situations.<br>
<br>
peace,<br>
