<br>
I can answer that Xzander. We only have a few necro's in our guild, but we take them and any others that may want to come if they want to come. I take every ranger I can that's of the proper level because almost all of our 55+ rangers have at least half of their epic and do quite a bit of damage that's usually 6 to 7 rangers we have available. We have one high level beastlord, and she comes on every raid she can along with the 4 high level mages we have. I take every pally i can so that i have at least one or two per group for the LH ability, their spells, and their high damage output...on average that's 6 to 9 pallies...and 3 to 5 sk's to go with them, 2 of which often do much of our pulling. I take all the druids I can get for nuking, buffing where needed, porting abilities and light healing...that's usually in the neighborhood of 4 to 6. I take as many wizzies as would like to go for unparalleled raw nuke ability to bring the bad guy down...usually between 1 and 4. We only have 3 rogues and only 1 that is high enough to raid the upper level raids, and I play him when we don't need me as a ST or TT.<br>
<br>
Now...it's pretty obvious by my statements that we take just about anyone when we go on a raid, within our guild and within our 5 (or maybe it's 6 now) guild alliance, that wants to go. We are not a tier1 or even a tier2 guild really. We go to have fun...loot is a very minor issue, and Taking down the mob is the concern, not how Few people we can take the mob down with. We merit to non guild members if they deserve it (we only merit bp's and robes) and we random everything else within the classes that can and will use it, regardless of guild/nonguild affiliation.<br>
<br>
I personally feel that this is the way it's done most of the time by most people on most of the servers. The End Game stuff everyone was been talking about really only applies to a very small percentage of people who can and are willing to join top tier raiding guilds, and who have the time to play for many many hours to grind out the xp's necessary for scads of AA pts. These people's concerns are just as valid as anyone elses, but aren't representative of the concerns of most of the rest of the server population, which is why I and many others don't want to see AA or equipment for warrior problems, but fundamental changes to the class itself. Fixing items or adding AA skills is only going to effect the small percentage of people that can get these ultra rare/difficult to obtain items or who have the time to grind out the xp's for the aa's.<br>
<br>
peace,<br>
Aielman KajiraLiege<br>
